# StoryFlow Leader's Guide: Scene List for {passage}

## Purpose
You are dividing {passage} into **natural story scenes** for group discussion. A scene may span multiple verses and should reflect **poetic movement, emotional flow, or thematic unity** — not merely verse-by-verse division.

## Resources

---

## Cultural Background

{exegetical_culture}

---

## Word Study Insights

{exegetical_wordstudy}

---

## Very Important Instructions

✅ You must output a **single valid JSON array**.

✅ No commentary, headings, explanations, or extra text — only the array.

✅ Inside the array, each scene must include exactly these fields:
- `"Scene number"`: e.g., "Scene 1", "Scene 2"
- `"Citation"`: e.g., "Psalm 23:1–3"
- `"Title"`: a short, vivid summary (3–8 words)
- `"Berean Standard Bible"`: the relevant verse text from the Berean Standard Bible
- `"WLC"`: the corresponding Hebrew text from the Westminster Leningrad Codex (WLC)

✅ **Escape all internal quotation marks (`"`) inside the Bible verses or WLC text fields** by using a backslash: `\"`.

✅ **You must NOT add any Markdown code fences** such as ```json or ```.

✅ **You must NOT add any commentary, summaries, headings, or explanations** — only output the JSON array.

✅ **If you detect that your output is invalid JSON, missing fields, has stray commas, missing quotation marks, or is improperly escaped, you must silently retry and regenerate a correct version without apology or commentary.**

✅ Do **not** default to one scene per verse. Group verses into scenes that share a **poetic, emotional, or imagistic unity**.

✅ If the passage begins with a poetic superscription (e.g., “A Psalm of David” / מִזְמוֹר לְדָוִד), treat it as **the opening of Scene 1**. Do not separate it from the main poetic movement.  

✅ Base scene breaks on **poetic, emotional, or imagistic shifts** — not just verse numbers or formatting conventions. A typical opening scene may include the superscription and verses 1–3 or more, depending on poetic unity.


✅ Format must be exactly like:

[
  {
    "Scene number": "Scene 1",
    "Citation": "Psalm 23:1–3",
    "Title": "The Shepherd Provides and Guides",
    "Berean Standard Bible": "A Psalm of David. The LORD is my shepherd; I shall not want. He makes me lie down in green pastures; He leads me beside quiet waters. He restores my soul; He guides me in paths of righteousness for His name’s sake.",
    "WLC": "מִזְמוֹר לְדָוִד יְהוָה רֹעִי לֹא אֶחְסָר׃ בִּנְאוֹת דֶּשֶׁא יַרְבִּיצֵנִי עַל מֵי מְנֻחוֹת יְנַהֲלֵנִי׃ נַפְשִׁי יְשׁוֹבֵב יַנְחֵנִי בְמַעְגְּלֵי צֶדֶק לְמַעַן שְׁמוֹ׃"
  }
]

